		<title>The history of marketing</title>
		<link href="https://example.com/blog/2016-08-12-the-history-of-marketing"/>
		<updated>2016-08-12T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
		<id>https://example.com/blog/2016-08-12-the-history-of-marketing</id>
		<content type="html">%3Cp%3EThe%20beginnings%20of%20digital%20marketing%20technology%20can%20be%20traced%20back%20to%20the%201980%27s%2C%20when%20computers%20became%20sophisticated%20enough%20to%20store%20huge%20volumes%20of%20customer%20information.%20For%20a%20brief%20moment%2C%20no%20one%20knew%20what%20would%20happen%20in%20digital%20marketing%2C%20but%20by%20the%2090%27s%20it%20all%20became%20clear.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%22https%3A//unsplash.it/960/600%3Fimage%3D133%22%20alt%3D%22Cars%22%3E%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20of%20marketing%20is%20to%20a%20large%20extent%20a%20product%20of%20Internet%27s%20history%20as%20markets%20have%20adapted%20to%20keep%20abreast%20of%20changes%20and%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20way%20the%20major%20Search%20Engines%20rank%20web%20pages.%20Major%20changes%20include%2C%20in%20chronological%20order%3A%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E1991-%20Gopher%3A%20A%20network%20protocol%2C%20one%20of%20the%20very%20first%20query%20and%20search%20tools.%20Gopher%20was%20widely%20used%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20but%20usage%20has%20now%20fallen%20off%2C%20with%20barely%20100%20Gopher%20servers%20now%20indexed.%202.%201994-%20Launch%20of%20Yahoo%2C%20which%20was%20formerly%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BJerry%B4s%20Guide%20to%20the%20World%20Wide%20Web%26quot%3B%20after%20one%20of%20its%20founders%2C%20Jerry%20Yang.%20Yahoo%20received%20in%20its%20first%20year%20over%201%20million%20hits.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Ch2%3EAcademic%20studies%3C/h2%3E%0A%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20of%20the%20history%20of%20marketing%20as%20an%20academic%20field%20emerged%20only%20recently.%20Controversies%20and%20disputes%20abound%20in%20the%20field.%20The%20publication%20in%201976%20of%20the%20book%20The%20History%20of%20Marketing%20Thought%2C%20by%20Robert%20Bartels%20marks%20a%20turning-point%20in%20marketing%20thought.%20Since%20then%2C%20academics%20specializing%20in%20marketing%20decided%20to%20imitate%20economics%2C%20distinguishing%20theory%20and%20practice.%20Two%20different%20fields%20of%20study%20emerged%3A%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3Ethe%20history%20of%20marketing%20thought%2C%20giving%20theoretical%20accounts%0Amarketing%20history%2C%20focusing%20on%20the%20history%20of%20marketing%20practice%0AThis%20division%20parallels%20the%20distinction%20between%20the%20history%20of%20economic%20thought%20and%20economic%20history.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%22https%3A//unsplash.it/960/600%3Fimage%3D175%22%20alt%3D%22Clock%22%3E%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3EPractitioners%20of%20the%20history%20of%20marketing%20thought%20note%20that%20both%20practitioners%20and%20academics%20know%20relatively%20little%20about%20the%20field.%5Bcitation%20needed%5D%20But%20history%20has%20significance%20for%20academics%20because%20it%20helps%20to%20define%20the%20baselines%20upon%20which%20they%20can%20recognize%20change%20and%20evolve%20marketing%20theory.On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20proponents%20of%20marketing%20history%20argue%20that%20one%20cannot%20fully%20compare%20the%20marketing%20field%20with%20economics%20and%20hence%20suggest%20the%20impracticality%20of%20divorcing%20theory%20and%20practice.%20First%2C%20marketing%20scholars%20seldom%20engage%20in%20the%20practice%20of%20marketing%20as%20much%20as%20economists%20engage%20in%20the%20development%20and%20execution%20of%20public%20policies.%20Second%2C%20business%20people%20innovate%20in%20the%20marketing%20field%2C%20and%20the%20history%20of%20marketing%20will%20remain%20incomplete%20if%20one%20dissociates%20academia%20from%20practitioners.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%22https%3A//unsplash.it/960/600%3Fimage%3D766%22%20alt%3D%22Coffee%22%3E%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20sections%20discuss%20both%20approaches%20to%20the%20history%20of%20marketing%2C%20closing%20with%20a%20debate%20about%20the%20standard%20chronology%20of%20marketing%2C%20a%20widely%20known%20hypothesis%20about%20the%20history%20of%20marketing%2C%20but%20one%20that%20historians%20in%20the%20marketing%20field%20have%20challenged.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_marketing%22%3Esource%3C/a%3E%3A%20Wikipedia%3C/p%3E%0A</content>
	</entry><entry>
		<title>Definition of sales</title>
		<link href="https://example.com/blog/2016-08-06-definition-of-sales"/>
		<updated>2016-08-06T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
		<id>https://example.com/blog/2016-08-06-definition-of-sales</id>
		<content type="html">%3Cp%3EA%20person%20or%20organization%20expressing%20an%20interest%20in%20acquiring%20the%20offered%20item%20of%20value%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20a%20potential%20buyer%2C%20prospective%20customer%20or%20prospect.%20Buying%20and%20selling%20are%20understood%20to%20be%20two%20sides%20of%20the%20same%20%26quot%3Bcoin%26quot%3B%20or%20transaction.%20Both%20seller%20and%20buyer%20engage%20in%20a%20process%20of%20negotiation%20to%20consummate%20the%20exchange%20of%20values.%20The%20exchange%2C%20or%20selling%2C%20process%20has%20implied%20rules%20and%20identifiable%20stages.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%22https%3A//unsplash.it/960/600%3Fimage%3D593%22%20alt%3D%22Tiger%22%3E%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20implied%20that%20the%20selling%20process%20will%20proceed%20fairly%20and%20ethically%20so%20that%20the%20parties%20end%20up%20nearly%20equally%20rewarded.%20The%20stages%20of%20selling%2C%20and%20buying%2C%20involve%20getting%20acquainted%2C%20assessing%20each%20party%u2019s%20need%20for%20the%20other%u2019s%20item%20of%20value%2C%20and%20determining%20if%20the%20values%20to%20be%20exchanged%20are%20equivalent%20or%20nearly%20so%2C%20or%2C%20in%20buyer%27s%20terms%2C%20%26quot%3Bworth%20the%20price.%u201D%20Sometimes%2C%20sellers%20have%20to%20use%20their%20own%20experiences%20when%20selling%20products%20with%20appropriate%20discounts.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Ch2%3EManagement%20point%20of%20view%3C/h2%3E%0A%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20management%20viewpoint%20it%20is%20thought%20of%20as%20a%20part%20of%20marketing%2C%20although%20the%20skills%20required%20are%20different.%20Sales%20often%20forms%20a%20separate%20grouping%20in%20a%20corporate%20structure%2C%20employing%20separate%20specialist%20operatives%20known%20as%20salespersons%20%28singular%3A%20salesperson%29.%20Selling%20is%20considered%20by%20many%20to%20be%20a%20sort%20of%20persuading%20%26quot%3Bart%26quot%3B.%20Contrary%20to%20popular%20belief%2C%20the%20methodological%20approach%20of%20selling%20refers%20to%20a%20systematic%20process%20of%20repetitive%20and%20measurable%20milestones%2C%20by%20which%20a%20salesman%20relates%20his%20or%20her%20offering%20of%20a%20product%20or%20service%20in%20return%20enabling%20the%20buyer%20to%20achieve%20their%20goal%20in%20an%20economic%20way.%20While%20the%20sales%20process%20refers%20to%20a%20systematic%20process%20of%20repetitive%20and%20measurable%20milestones%2C%20the%20definition%20of%20the%20selling%20is%20somewhat%20ambiguous%20due%20to%20the%20close%20nature%20of%20advertising%2C%20promotion%2C%20public%20relations%2C%20and%20direct%20marketing.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%22https%3A//unsplash.it/960/600%3Fimage%3D672%22%20alt%3D%22Bus%22%3E%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3ESelling%20is%20the%20profession-wide%20term%2C%20much%20like%20marketing%20defines%20a%20profession.%20Recently%2C%20attempts%20have%20been%20made%20to%20clearly%20understand%20who%20is%20in%20the%20sales%20profession%2C%20and%20who%20is%20not.%20There%20are%20many%20articles%20looking%20at%20marketing%2C%20advertising%2C%20promotions%2C%20and%20even%20public%20relations%20as%20ways%20to%20create%20a%20unique%20transaction.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Ch2%3ECommon%20terms%3C/h2%3E%0A%3Cp%3ETwo%20common%20terms%20used%20to%20describe%20a%20salesperson%20are%20%26quot%3BFarmer%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BHunter%26quot%3B.%20The%20reality%20is%20that%20most%20professional%20sales%20people%20have%20a%20little%20of%20both.%20A%20hunter%20is%20often%20associated%20with%20aggressive%20personalities%20who%20use%20aggressive%20sales%20technique.%20In%20terms%20of%20sales%20methodology%20a%20hunter%20refers%20to%20a%20person%20whose%20focus%20is%20on%20bringing%20in%20and%20closing%20deals.%20This%20process%20is%20called%20%u201Csales%20capturing%u201D.%20An%20example%20is%20a%20commodity%20sale%20such%20as%20a%20long%20distance%20sales%20person%2C%20shoe%20sales%20person%20and%20to%20a%20degree%20a%20car%20sales%20person.%20Their%20job%20is%20to%20find%20and%20convert%20buyers.%20A%20sales%20farmer%20is%20someone%20who%20creates%20sales%20demand%20by%20activities%20that%20directly%20influence%20and%20alter%20the%20buying%20process.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%22https%3A//unsplash.it/960/600%3Fimage%3D1027%22%20alt%3D%22Person%22%3E%3C/p%3E%0A%3Ch2%3ESystems%20approach%3C/h2%3E%0A%3Cp%3EMany%20believe%20that%20the%20focus%20of%20selling%20is%20on%20the%20human%20agents%20involved%20in%20the%20exchange%20between%20buyer%20and%20seller.%20Effective%20selling%20also%20requires%20a%20systems%20approach%2C%20at%20minimum%20involving%20roles%20that%20sell%2C%20enable%20selling%2C%20and%20develop%20sales%20capabilities.%20Selling%20also%20involves%20salespeople%20who%20possess%20a%20specific%20set%20of%20sales%20skills%20and%20the%20knowledge%20required%20to%20facilitate%20the%20exchange%20of%20value%20between%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20that%20is%20unique%20from%20marketing%2C%20advertising%2C%20etc.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%22https%3A//unsplash.it/960/600%3Fimage%3D601%22%20alt%3D%22Plant%22%3E%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3EWithin%20these%20three%20tenets%2C%20the%20following%20definition%20of%20professional%20selling%20is%20offered%20by%20the%20American%20Society%20for%20Training%20and%20Development%20%28ASTD%29%3A%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%u201CThe%20holistic%20business%20system%20required%20to%20effectively%20develop%2C%20manage%2C%20enable%2C%20and%20execute%20a%20mutually%20beneficial%2C%20interpersonal%20exchange%20of%20goods%20and/or%20services%20for%20equitable%20value.%u201D%0ATeam%20selling%20is%20one%20way%20to%20influence%20sales.%20Team%20selling%20is%20%u201Ca%20group%20of%20people%20representing%20the%20sales%20department%20and%20other%20functional%20areas%20in%20the%20firm%2C%20such%20as%20finance%2C%20production%2C%20and%20research%20and%20development%u201D.%20%28Spiro%29%20Team%20selling%20came%20about%20in%20the%201990s%20through%20total%20quality%20management%20%28TQM%29.%20TQM%20occurs%20when%20companies%20work%20to%20improve%20their%20customer%20satisfaction%20by%20constantly%20improving%20all%20of%20their%20operations.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sales%22%3Esource%3C/a%3E%3A%20Wikipedia%3C/p%3E%0A</content>
	</entry><entry>
		<title>Effective upselling techniques</title>
		<link href="https://example.com/blog/2016-07-28-effective-upselling-techniques"/>
		<updated>2016-07-28T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
		<id>https://example.com/blog/2016-07-28-effective-upselling-techniques</id>
		<content type="html">%3Cp%3EUpselling%20is%20a%20sales%20technique%20whereby%20a%20seller%20induces%20the%20customer%20to%20purchase%20more%20expensive%20items%2C%20upgrades%20or%20other%20add-ons%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20make%20a%20more%20profitable%20sale.%20While%20it%20usually%20involves%20marketing%20more%20profitable%20services%20or%20products%2C%20it%20can%20be%20simply%20exposing%20the%20customer%20to%20other%20options%20that%20were%20perhaps%20not%20considered.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3EIn%20practice%2C%20large%20businesses%20usually%20combine%20upselling%20and%20cross-selling%20to%20maximize%20profit.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20an%20organization%20must%20ensure%20that%20its%20relationship%20with%20the%20client%20is%20not%20disrupted.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%22https%3A//unsplash.it/960/600%3Fimage%3D590%22%20alt%3D%22Seaside%20City%22%3E%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3EIn%20restaurants%20and%20other%20similar%20settings%2C%20upselling%20is%20commonplace%20and%20an%20accepted%20form%20of%20business.%20In%20other%20businesses%20%28e.g.%20car%20sales%29%2C%20the%20customer%u2019s%20perception%20of%20the%20attempted%20upsell%20can%20be%20viewed%20negatively%20and%20impact%20the%20desired%20result.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Ch2%3EWhy%20should%20you%20upsell%3F%3C/h2%3E%0A%3Cp%3EUpselling%20is%20a%20common%20practice%20for%20service%20providers%20that%20offer%20different%20service%20classes%20such%20as%20airlines%20%28cf.%20Bohutinsky%2C%201990%29.%20According%20to%20%u201Cthe%20journal%20of%20business%20and%20industrial%20marketing%3B%20written%20collaboratively%20by%20Michael%20J%2C%20Sheehan%20and%20Paul%20R%2C%20Prabhaker%20%u201CIt%20is%20five%20times%20more%20expensive%20to%20get%20a%20new%20customer%20as%20it%20is%20to%20hold%20onto%20a%20current%20one.%u201D%20Selling%20to%20a%20new%20customer%20would%20mean%20having%20to%20start%20the%20sales%20process%20from%20the%20very%20beginning%20thus%20having%20to%20establish%20a%20new%20relationship%20with%20a%20different%20customer.%20This%20can%20be%20time%20consuming%20and%20often%20not%20very%20effective.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%22https%3A//unsplash.it/960/600%3Fimage%3D1043%22%20alt%3D%22Landscape%22%3E%3C/p%3E%0A%3Ch2%3EThe%20benefits%3C/h2%3E%0A%3Cp%3EUpselling%20to%20a%20customer%20that%20you%20have%20already%20built%20a%20rapport%20with%2C%20means%20that%20they%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20buy%20from%20you%2C%20listen%20to%20your%20suggestions%20and%20opinions%20and%20trust%20you.%20Selling%20to%20the%20same%20customer%20can%20lead%20to%20loyal%20customers%20and%20repeat%20sales.%20Upselling%20brings%20up%20the%20profit%20that%20the%20business%20makes%20and%20the%20value%20of%20the%20sale.%20However%20it%20is%20important%20to%20understand%20that%20although%20your%20main%20objective%20is%20to%20bring%20up%20revenue%20and%20increase%20the%20amount%20of%20the%20sale%2C%20a%20customers%20experience%20and%20their%20time%20with%20you%20influences%20future%20decisions%20that%20they%20make.%20An%20upsell%20can%20be%20beneficial%20to%20both%20the%20seller%20and%20the%20consumer%20if%20relevant%20products%20are%20being%20shown%20to%20the%20customer.%20For%20instance%2C%20if%20you%20had%20a%20strict%20budget%20of%20%2420%2C000%20for%20a%20car%2C%20you%20would%20not%20want%20to%20be%20sold%20a%20car%20for%20twice%20the%20amount.%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Upselling%22%3Esource%3C/a%3E%3A%20Wikipedia%3C/p%3E%0A</content>
